   "source": [
    "## Introduction\n",
    "\n",
    "The rapid growth of data generated from digital platforms has significantly increased the demand for distributed data processing and scalable storage technologies. Traditional relational database management systems are often insufficient for handling large scale datasets efficiently particularly when high processing speed, fault tolerance and scalability are required. Consequently, big data frameworks such as Apache Hadoop, Apache Spark and Apache Cassandra have become essential technologies for modern data engineering and analytics. Hadoop Distributed File System (HDFS) provides reliable distributed storage, Apache Spark enables efficient in-memory distributed computation while Apache Cassandra offers highly scalable NoSQL data storage for managing structured and semi-structured data.\n",
    "\n",
    "This assignment demonstrates the implementation of an end to end big data processing pipeline using the MovieLens 100K dataset. The dataset contains information about movie ratings, user demographic profiles and movie metadata making it a suitable benchmark for demonstrating distributed data processing techniques. The workflow begins by storing the raw dataset within HDFS followed by transforming the raw text files into Spark Resilient Distributed Datasets (RDDs) and structured DataFrames. Spark SQL is then utilised to perform several analytical tasks including movie rating analysis and user demographic filtering. Finally, the processed DataFrames are stored within Apache Cassandra and subsequently retrieved to validate the successful integration between Apache Spark and Cassandra.\n",
    "\n",
    "The primary objective of this assignment is to demonstrate the practical integration of distributed storage, distributed processing, SQL based analytics and NoSQL database management within a single big data ecosystem. The implementation not only illustrates the technical capabilities of Apache Spark and Cassandra but also highlights how distributed computing technologies can efficiently process large datasets while maintaining scalability, fault tolerance and high performance."
   ]
  },
  {
