    "## Environment Setup\n",
    "\n",
    "A distributed big data environment was prepared prior to performing the analytical tasks. The implementation was conducted using the Hortonworks Data Platform (HDP) Sandbox which provides an integrated ecosystem consisting of Hadoop Distributed File System (HDFS), Apache Spark, Apache Hive, Apache Cassandra and other Hadoop ecosystem components. This environment enables seamless communication between distributed storage and distributed processing frameworks without requiring additional system configuration.\n",
    "\n",
    "The implementation was developed using Python together with the PySpark library to facilitate distributed data processing. Apache Spark SQL was utilised to execute analytical queries while the Spark Cassandra Connector was incorporated to enable data exchange between Spark DataFrames and Apache Cassandra tables. The connector package was specified during the execution of the Spark application using the spark-submit command to ensure compatibility between Spark 2.x and Cassandra.\n",
    "\n",
    "The software configuration used throughout this assignment is summarised below.\n",
    "| Component | Version/Description |\n",
    "|--------|-----------|\n",
    "|Programming Language | Python|\n",
    "|Apache Spark | Spark 2.x (HDP Sandbox)|\n",
    "|Apache Hadoop | HDP Sandbox|\n",
    "|Distributed Storage | HDFS|\n",
    "|NoSQL Database | Apache Cassandra 3.x|\n",
    "|Query Engine | Spark SQL|\n",
    "|Spark Connector | DataStax Spark Cassandra Connector 2.4.3|\n",
    "|Development Environment | PuTTY (SSH Terminal)|\n",
    "\n",
    "After the environment had been configured successfully, the required Python libraries were imported including the PySpark SQL libraries, SparkSession, DataFrame schema definitions and the Python subprocess module for executing Cassandra commands programmatically. Establishing the environment correctly ensures that the subsequent data processing pipeline operates consistently throughout the assignment."
   ]
