    "## Data Loading\n",
    "\n",
    "The MovieLens 100K dataset was selected as the primary dataset for this assignment due to its structured format and suitability for demonstrating distributed data processing techniques. The dataset consists of three main files namely u.user, u.data and u.item representing user demographic information, movie ratings and movie metadata respectively.\n",
    "\n",
    "Prior to performing any analysis, the dataset files were uploaded into the Hadoop Distributed File System (HDFS). Storing the dataset within HDFS enables Apache Spark to access the files directly using distributed storage, thereby supporting efficient parallel processing across the computing environment. The uploaded files were organised under the directory /user/maria_dev/movielens100k ensuring consistent file management throughout the assignment.\n",
    "\n",
    "The data loading process was performed by creating Spark Context objects to read each dataset file from HDFS. Initially, each file was loaded as a Resilient Distributed Dataset (RDD) which represents Spark's fundamental distributed data structure. The RDD abstraction allows data to be partitioned across multiple processing units while maintaining fault tolerance through lineage information. Each record was subsequently parsed using the appropriate delimiter based on the dataset format before being converted into structured records.\n",
    "\n",
    "Explicit schemas were then defined for the users, ratings and movies datasets. Rather than relying on automatic schema inference, manually specifying the schema improves data consistency, enhances readability and ensures that each attribute is assigned the correct data type. The structured RDDs were subsequently transformed into Spark DataFrames allowing SQL based operations to be performed efficiently using Spark SQL. This transformation also facilitates integration with Apache Cassandra during the later stages of the assignment."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "99862a7c-4178-4ba5-91f5-f63ae277b9b6",
