   "source": [
    "## Data Preprocessing\n",
    "\n",
    "Data preprocessing was performed to improve data quality and ensure consistency before executing analytical queries. Although the MovieLens dataset is relatively clean, several preprocessing operations were still applied to guarantee the reliability of the analytical results.\n",
    "\n",
    "The first preprocessing step involved validating the completeness of each dataset after loading. The total number of records was verified to ensure that all data had been successfully imported from HDFS into Spark. The expected dataset consists of 943 user records, 100,000 movie rating records and 1,682 movie records. Confirming these record counts provides assurance that no data loss occurred during the loading process.\n",
    "\n",
    "Subsequently, duplicate records were removed from the DataFrames using Spark's dropDuplicates() function. Duplicate removal prevents repeated observations from influencing subsequent statistical analysis and aggregation results. Appropriate primary key attributes were used for each dataset to preserve data integrity while eliminating redundant records.\n",
    "\n",
    "Following duplicate removal, the predefined schemas were validated to ensure that numerical attributes such as user identifiers, movie identifiers, ratings and timestamps were correctly stored as integer data types whereas textual attributes such as occupation, gender, movie title and release date were represented as string variables. Maintaining consistent data types is essential for enabling accurate aggregation, filtering and join operations during Spark SQL analysis.\n",
    "\n",
    "Finally, the cleaned DataFrames were registered as temporary SQL views within Spark. Registering the DataFrames as temporary views enables Spark SQL to execute relational queries using familiar SQL syntax while leveraging Spark's distributed processing capabilities. These temporary views serve as the primary data sources for all subsequent analytical tasks performed throughout this assignment."
   ]
