    "Task 4 focuses on identifying users who are below 20 years of age by applying a demographic filtering operation using Apache Spark SQL. The query extracts user records that satisfy the condition age < 20 providing a subset of younger users from the MovieLens dataset. The filtered results were subsequently stored in the task4_young_users table within Apache Cassandra to demonstrate the integration between Spark SQL and a NoSQL database. The validation query SELECT COUNT(*) confirms that the table contains 77 records indicating that 77 users in the dataset are younger than 20 years old. This confirms that the filtering process was executed correctly and that all qualifying records were successfully written to Cassandra.\n",
    "\n",
    "The identification of younger users provides valuable demographic insights that can support user segmentation and personalised recommendation strategies. Age is a significant factor influencing viewing preferences, content consumption patterns and recommendation effectiveness. By isolating users under the age of 20, organisations can analyse the preferences and behaviour of younger audiences separately from other demographic groups enabling more targeted content recommendations and marketing strategies. Furthermore, this analysis demonstrates the capability of Apache Spark SQL to perform efficient demographic filtering on large scale datasets while utilising Apache Cassandra for scalable storage and retrieval of processed analytical results. The successful extraction and validation of 77 young users illustrate the effectiveness of the implemented data pipeline in supporting demographic analysis within a distributed big data environment."
